text:
herstory: una historia ilustrada de las mujeres.

nacho moreno 
maría bastarós 
cristina daura

editorial lumen

la historia del feminismo, desde la prehistoria hasta #metoo.

aunque quede mucho por hacer para que una mujer pueda moverse por el mundo con los mismos derechos que un hombre, se ha recorrido ya un largo camino: a diferencia de los hombres, sus derechos no son inherentes a su condición de mujer, sino que han sido adquiridos gracias a una constante lucha. 
cada pellizco de dignidad femenina ha sido conquistado por figuras determinantes, cuyos rostros no siempre han sido reconocidos. 
este libro cuenta una historia tan larga como la de la humanidad y da voz a los miles de movimientos necesarios para llegar al estado actual.

@penguinrandomhouse
@maria_bastaros
@cdaura

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy a

text:
l’isgb rapportera 3 millards par an, selon bercy, qui table sur 300’000 français assujettis à l’isgb. l’administration effectuera des contrôles et observera les réseaux sociaux pour détecter les fraudeurs. l’opposition craint une fuite des grosses bites à l’étranger. «n’oublions pas que celles et ceux qui ont des grosses bites font beaucoup de bien autour d’elles ou d’eux», a déclaré ségolène royal, qui a poursuivi: «personne ne souhaite que ce soit les belges ou les suisses qui profitent de tous ces bienfaits.» najat vallaud belkacem, au contraire, soutient la réforme: «je ne crois pas à la théorie du ruissellement (ndlr: théorie qui dit que coulent des grosses bites des gouttes qui descendent ensuite et qui vont irriguer toute la société)», a tweeté mme vallaud belckacem. le gouvernement espère, grâce à l’isgb, satisfaire l’aspiration des gilets jaunes à plus d’équité. «le compte n’y est pas», a déclaré m.mélenchon, tout rouge et en colère, «on ne nous donne que des miettes, 1% au dessus de 18 cms, de qui se moque macron?, le peuple ne sera rassasié que lorsqu’il recevra son dû. moi, au dessus de 18 cms, je prends tout.»

text: my friend and fellow blogger, @kickinitkowalski, gifted me this book "100 days to brave" and at first i said i'd start it in the new year. and then i thought... why not now?? so, i started the day it arrived it in the mail. each day features a short, 1-2 page anecdote centered around being #brave. at the end, there is a daily challenge. day 3 challenge was to journal about one or two moments in your life that you or someone else might label as brave. i journaled about 1) how people tell me i'm brave to write blogs so openly (like my vulnerability in my #metoo #believesurvivors blog) and 2) how i quit the job i hated, packed up my things, and moved away from home in order to pursue a #life as a full-time blogger. i am loving this gift of daily reflection and heightened self-awareness, and although i feel brave in many respects, i am so excited to see how brave i feel on day 100. #liveuntamed #loveuntamed #untamedmelodies

text:
nos veo en la lágrima que desborda de impotencia, de furia. 
nos veo en el abrazo, en la sororidad. 
me veo en cada historia que me llega, que escucho, que leo. 
me veo sentada hablando con otras mujeres sobre lo mismo, en el "avisame cuando llegues" traducido en un "quiero que sigas viva". nos veo en el enojo de las pibas, de todas, vulneradas, silenciadas, oprimidas. 
a mi me abusaron a los seis años de edad. a los quince me di cuenta qué era lo que quería hacer el tipo conmigo, hace menos de un año que, con dolor, pude ponerle la palabra que lleva: abuso. 
yo también pase momentos de mierda en donde mi integridad era vulnerada. "loca de mierd*" me han gritado por putear a alguno que piropeaba en la calle, que me tocaba la cola a la pasada. 
el poder de muchas alimenta. 
esto es solo el comienzo. 
por todas nosotras, justicia. y si la justicia no responde (como viene haciendo, la ausencia del estado), se hará justicia social. 
ya no nos callan.
no es no, no es un "convenceme". sobre mi cuerpo decido yo! 
harta de que nos violen, nos maten, nos peguen, nos excluyan. 
harta de que la justicia mire para otro lado, harta de la ausencia del estado. 
te metes con una, respondemos todas. 
fuerza y lucha 💚✊. organizadas podemos!
#miracomonosponemos 
#seráley 
#noesno
#metoo

me veo sentada hablando con otras mujeres sobre lo mismo, en el "avisame cuando llegues" traducido en un "quiero que sigas viva". nos veo en el enojo de las pibas, de todas, vulneradas, silenciadas, oprimidas. 
a mi me abusaron a los seis años de edad. a los quince me di cuenta qué era lo que quería hacer el tipo conmigo, hace menos de un año que, con dolor, pude ponerle la palabra que lleva: abuso. 
yo también pase momentos de mierda en donde mi integridad era vulnerada. "loca de mierd*" me han gritado por putear a alguno que piropeaba en la calle, que me tocaba la cola a la pasada. 
el poder de muchas alimenta. 
esto es solo el comienzo. 
por todas nosotras, justicia. y si la justicia no responde (como viene haciendo, la ausencia del estado), se hará justicia social. 
ya no nos callan.
no es no, no es un "convenceme". sobre mi cuerpo decido yo! 
harta de que nos violen, nos maten, nos peguen, nos excluyan. 
harta de que la justicia mire para otro lado, harta de la ausencia del estado. 
te metes con una, respondemos todas. 
fuerza y lucha 💚✊. organizadas podemos!

text:
never too late to help... #metoo - the girl over there, had her teeth clenched and fists closed, everytime she had dawned upon a dirty road.

#metoo - yes, the women to your left have checked their full sleeves to see if any skin was dripping, any flaws or even if any bare tooth was too revealing.

#metoo - the girlfriend in the corner has been called a fool because she was naked with a man who used her as a tool.

#metoo - the daughter in the future, will learn that her father, too, had referred, once in a while, "casually though", women as sluts and unhinged whores.

#youaswell - listen close and you'll hear the muffled cries, from women around you that you don't usually bother.

it's time to stop chasing butterflies, open eyes, and offer kindness and only kindness, to one another.

help cyntoia browns
and donna does.
those from the list that, sadly, could go for a row or more.

text:
“not having enough of”...is sometimes a real situation, that requires a person to wake up and begin making changes to live a more manageable life.  however, most times this way of thinking is simply an “excuse” or a “distorted” state of the mind. 
we can truly experience freedom, happiness and success in our life; we can truly feel what self love & worth feel like, and we can absolutely achieve anything it is that we are able to close our eyes and see in the darkness of our minds.  enriching the soils of our inner gardens each day is essential to reaching this vibrational level, which is essential to healing yourself with your own powerful energy!  #selfgarden #fertilizedsoil #healingenergy #unconditionallove #selfacceptance. 
abundance is also a state of mind; of “having enough of, or having more than enough to be content.” this is all i need to feel joy & gratitude each and every day.🙌🙏🧘‍♀️🥰#abundancementality #flipside #iamenough #selfgarden #karma #recovery #spiritualityofimperfection #taoteching #kundalini #selflove #metoo #timesup #endthesilence #enddomesticviolence #povertyisastateofmind #abundanceistheanswer @myocoyotzin #notthatkindofday

text:
our first blog post! 📖
.
the past week has been triggering for myself and so many women i know. the mind and body are connected: if the mind is not well, the body is not well (and vice versa). it’s so important we we work on both our mental and physical health because they go hand-in-hand.
.
one of the best tools i use is journaling ✍️ i’ve learned that journaling is a life changing practice. if you think journaling can help you, please read our first blog post! link is in the bio ❤️✨
.
#blog #journaling #healthylifestyle #wellness #mindbodysoul

《那天清晨我在海邊將自己葬下》
『「男性凝視」的基本論調是：男人觀看，而女人就是被觀看被控制的對象，而男人從觀看中得到快感。這一種的觀看形式，就是一種權力的展現。』——截自網路
在父權體系中，女性展露自己的身體始終是被壓迫的。我們都是吃了禁果的人類，所以才為裸體感到羞恥。
當打破了父權體制，打破了女性身體物化的框架，所有的裸體才會被視為自然，神所創造的，最天然的藝術品。

text:
shabana azmi is not only well-known for her nuanced acting skills but also for her bold activism. she made her film debut movie ankur in 1974 and became one of the leading actresses of parallel cinema - a new-wave movement is known for its serious content & neo-realism and received govt patronage during the 1970s and 80s. 
she has won many international & national accolades for portraying different characters and exploring different facets of women and indian society, its customs and traditions through a progressive lens. she also fights for the rights of the poor and the downtrodden in india. she is a goodwill ambassador for the united nations population  fund and also a member of the rajya sabha. she has also been awarded the padma shri as well as padma bhushan by the indian govt. 
she is not afraid of taking up controversial or offbeat roles; her poise and polished skills won her praise for realistically portraying all the characters that she played, while her choice of string characters also brought criticism and outrage to her door. 
sanfe salutes her for lending her celebrity status to several social causes such as campaigns against ostracizing victims of aids, for voicing her opinions and supporting woman's rights despite facing flak from certain quarters.

share this post & tag @sanfeindia in order to get free samples of sanfe. 
#standupforyourself

text:
finishing line press book of the day:
when you finally said no by kathie giorgio $14.99, paper

https://www.finishinglinepress.com/product/when-you-finally-said-no-by-kathie-giorgio/

kathie giorgio, a pushcart nominee, is the critically acclaimed author of four novels, two story collections, an essay collection and two poetry chapbooks. her short stories, poems and essays have appeared in countless literary magazines and anthologies. her short story, snapdragon, was performed on stage for the stories on stage series at su teatro theatre in boulder, colorado. giorgio is the director/founder of allwriters’ workplace & workshop llc. “kathie giorgio’s poems sear and sizzle. they gut punch with harsh truths—“when you sit at your mirror / forever after a rape / you are not your reflection.” giorgio’s is a voice we need in the #metoo movement. these poems stand for innumerable women who have been silenced for centuries, and we are so very lucky to have them now.
–shaindel beers, author of secure your own mask, winner of the white pine poetry prize “here are poems written maturely and wisely, yet with unflinching honesty that never steers off track, but keeps moving through a poetic chronology of hauntings, consequences, and self-reconciliation. the precise language, often percussive and lyrical, keeps the momentum going.  kathie giorgio creates allusions using nature, such as the sea gull who is like the raped girl, or the seasons, with summer lost to internal winter. a grey t-shirt becomes a symbol for a fearful, suffering self-image. accessible, authoritative, stark without ranting, crisp staccato phrasing with forays into haiku and villanelle—a varied collection recalling clearly what it means to be a victim who does not deny the experience, but embraces it, expressed with artistic fullness.”
–christine swanberg, author of wild fruition, the alleluia tree, who walks among the trees with charity “kathie giorgio’s when you finally said no arrives at the right time. these poems are mirror and microphone both, as the words stretch to find language to speak what has previously been unspeakable...#metoo #poetry

text: yesterday in my room i heard a train knowing there isn’t one nearby. i thought i was hearing things. next my step dad came in to show me the props he was using to read a story to first graders. one being a pocket watch, he said turn it over. there was a train on it. i thought what? led by the spirit i looked up what a train symbolizes. it said: trains symbolize your life’s journey, it suggests that you are on the right track in life and headed in the right direction. alternatively it means you have a tendency to worry needlessly over a situation that will work out in the end. as of late i have been concerned about my current situation and where my life is headed and or what’s next. as i was walking out to get in my truck there it was again loud and clear the sound of a train. having a relationship with god is full of encounters just like that, he has creative unexpected ways to communicate with us if we chose to believe and invite him into our lives. you may call it coincidence but i call it a touch from god making it a godincident. my heart is full of joy that only he can give. not knowing where my life is headed but learning to enjoy the ride. #hope #faith #joy #love #myblinddatewithgod #coincidence #godincidence #holyspirit #touched #jesus #relationship #john316 #metoo #shine #thrive #novictim #survivor #journey #enjoytheride #destination #acquitted #414ministry

text:
актриса наталья варлей, сыгравшая студентку нину в фильме «кавказская пленница», рассказала, что режиссер леонид гайдай, якобы, приставал к ней в период съемок, в отеле. об этом со ссылкой на ее мемуары написала газета «комсомольская правда». по словам «нины», что в один день они отмечали день рождения «шурика» (александра демьяненко). режиссер гайдай провожал варлей до гостиницы, и зашел вместе с нею в ее номер, попытался закрыться с нею внутри. но к этому времени на этаж поднялась супруга гайдая, и вошла в ее номер.

из-за неловкости ситуации варлей сказала ей, что «мы работаем», жена режиссера ушла. и вот тут, уходя, он, якобы, попытался поцеловать актрису, но она увернулась и выставила его за дверь.

супруга режиссера нина гребешкова в своем комментарии сми была кратка. она предложила спросить правда ли это или нет у самого гайдая, которого, правда уже 25 лет как нет в живых.

наблюдатели отмечают, что признание варлей созвучно тем признаниям, что дают актрисы кино на западе, включая громкий процесс вокруг кинорежиссера харви ванштейна. он способствовал росту феминистического онлайн-движения с хэштегом #metoo. 
кинокритик давид шнейдеров счел слова варлей «мерзкими». он считает, что такие тенденции признаний актрис в кино и театре вредные и предвзятые. «я не понимаю, что сегодня происходит в мире. движение #metoo я не просто не поддерживаю, я считаю, что они уродуют судьбы, калечат людей. за изнасилование есть уголовная статья, а если они сами отдавались мужикам за гонорары или за «оскар», то это их проблемы», — цитирует его gazeta.ru.

на фото - скришот из к/ф "кавказская пленница"

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
to that women who made me independent, 
to the women who never gave up on me, 
someone who taught me never to be scared,
the one who balances our house and still no one bothers. 
dont break her wings, instead give her reasons to fly, 
dont tell them to sit properly, try to be a better person. 
dont tell them to wear full sleeves, instead change your perception.

not every womens desire are fulfilled, 
she gives away her needs to accomplish your greeds. 
her smile can make miracles, even after she gets wrinkles. 
respect her beacause you will get every type of women in your phases of your life. 
mom, teacher,daughter and sister they add charm to your life. 
the one who makes your life worth living, 
cause they have a smile worth fighting for.
.
.

text: i would like to invite you all to @facetgallery tomorrow night for "paint like a girl", the 4th annual all womens' art show benefiting wellspring living, a nonprofit organization devoted to safeguarding and empowering domestic sex trafficking victims. wellspring is dedicated to serving those at risk of exploitation to develop the courage to move forward and the confidence to succeed. i am honored to be one of the artists included in this show. two of my original cow-ladies, calcium and maneater, will be on display along with a snowy-white schmoopie. huge thanks to @aliyailsa for putting me on the radar for this show and to @kayleenscott for organizing and curating. i hope you will join us at 7:00 pm for this amazing night of women's art for a great cause! 💟♀️😘💪♀️💟

text:
. 🌪keep clear ⛅️ .
this time of year can cause a rise in #anxiety . i know it does for me! 
routines go out the window, lots of talking and socialising, fear of changes in the new year, weather getting colder for most of us! 
so, it’s really important to keep as much of you clear as possible. try a full day or 1 meal a day (ideally a full week) that is clean, nutritious and free from toxins like refined sugar and white flour. reduce caffeine, careful on the alcohol, write it out, talk to someone or find a #mantra . these last 3 really help. anxiety normally comes from a sense of unknown, difficult to pin point a cause. so write down your thoughts and worries. find a mantra. give yourself a positive affirmation. “this feeling is only temporary” or “i am strong and all is well ;) you know.
.
what are yours???🧡
.
.

text:
#metoo has shown that there is still a very, very long way to go. but there is no denying that i have more rights and opportunities than my grandmothers, or even my mother enjoyed. for as long as i can remember, i have been aware of this. i have always been determined not to take my rights and opportunities for granted and i never will. 
but, i am afraid, that before i was a mum, i did take the wonder of motherhood for granted. not now. bearing a child is a superpower reserved for us girls. and as superpowers go, it is pretty awesome! (if occasionally icky). time to explore nature's part in helping me become a mum!

text:
"porque no hay un tiempo posible para reconocer las experiencias que han sido abusivas y recomponernos, también para poder lograr una denuncia. nosotras decimos y sabemos que nunca es tarde" "mirá cómo nos ponemos" es un grito colectivo al abusivo, culpabilizador y cada vez más solitario “mirá como me ponés”, también para el resto de los varones cisheterosexuales, un límite y una advertencia.
"mirá cómo nos ponemos" es una respuesta positiva y cada vez más empoderada a la cultura de la violación que nos dice que de eso no hay que hablar.

mirá cómo nos ponemos es salir del lugar de la victima por el de lx sobreviviente.

a los violadores, abusadores y machistas les respondemos con organización y avanzada feminista. 
mirá cómo nos ponemos fuertes 
mirá cómo nos ponemos libres
mirá cómo nos ponemos juntas

el abuso no prescribe

mirá como nos ponemos ¡el patriarcado se va a caer porque lo vamos a tirar!

#miracomonosponemos #mirabien #yotecreo #abajoelpatriarcado #sevaacaer #lovamosatirar
#feminismo #feminist #metoo #quimeras #noesno #noestassola

text_retweet:
#repost @las12pagina12 (@get_repost)
・・・
lo que pasó el martes en multiteatro merece una celebración. es el resultado de años de militancia, puesta en común de prácticas y una escucha atenta del feminismo a las mujeres y disidencias que padecen las violencias machistas. también es el dolor que circula cuando sabemos que todas fuimos abusadas, de una u otra manera, y que al mismo tiempo que podemos decirlo vemos a los varones pararse de manos y replegarse en una actitud tribal: “yo nunca le pegué a nadie” parecen decir, o dicen de hecho.

de ese conjunto de experiencias de activismo, puesta de cuerpos en la calle y palabras para nombrar lo que no tiene nombre se gestó ni una menos, la pelea por el aborto legal y los paros de mujeres que se hicieron en este país e irradiaron su potencia a toda latinoamérica, al mundo.

la insistencia con apelar al #metoo como hashtag explicativo y protector de una causa de la que podemos dar cátedra, molesta e incomoda, porque no hay #metoo argentino, hay un movimiento con una historia propia, que peleó por tomar la palabra aun cuando ésta estaba prohibida, y pienso en nuestras desaparecidas, en las madres y abuelas con su ritual de ronda y en las militantes que se hicieron en los ochenta con la propia experiencia y ese ruido constante a injusticia que recae sobre las identidades mujer, lesbiana, trans, travesti.

por @calistapunch

text: i can’t count the times i felt ashamed, scared or simply abused for being a woman. the first time i was 15. it was during a holiday trip at a club med with my friends’s family. one random night a guy locked me in his room and touched me inappropriately (that’s a nice way to put it). i got back to my room and spewed all my dinner, dealing with all this shame and nausea, i got back to sleep. i am lucky, i thought, he didn’t actually raped me. my friend got mad at me because i got back so late, she never knew what happened and -at the time- i decided not to share this with anyone. years later i mentioned the episode, casually, to my therapist: “im sorry you were abused”...wait, what? no! im not a victim! i hated the victim mentality and the idea of making a scene, i was afraid of people thinking “she just wants some attention” and -ironically- that became my biggest fear ....and i learned to “keep it private”, because that’s what good girls do. i learned to be good so i said nothing when at college that guy grabbed my butt and laughed - @travel.ry apologized years later, it takes also courage to acknowledge you were wrong - and as a professional, i had to endure the senior -married with 4 kids- guy harassing me over text for months, the investor making me jump off the moving cab, the married client proposing trips to bahamas to “discuss business”...and the endless list of small daily ill-treatments. if you think that in america is bad (ask dr blasey-ford how bad it can be!), in latin america is even worse. machos, all-boys clubs (hello nike!), entitlement, impunity everywhere. all i got every time i tried to speak up was a clear “please, don’t make a scene”. women should speak up for other women to have the courage to do the same, to know they are not the ones to blame. women have been historically oppressed and part of it it’s the fact that we find it very difficult to work together, to team up and be one body screaming #timesup #metoo #patriarchy #maledomination #sevaacaer #proud #stopabuse #socialresponsibility #miracomonosponemos

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this is @taranajaneen , founder of the #metoo movement. did you all know that she started it in 2006 when she was working with teens of color and realized how prevalent sexual assault was within their community? when she spoke at the facing race conference, she urged us to learn the facts. facts like how 1/4 girls and 1/6 boys and 84% of trans women experience sexual harassment each year. native women are 3.5 times more likely to experience this and people with disabilities are 7x more likely. 60% of black girls will experience sexual assault by the time they are 18. take a moment to let that sink in. 
she needed us to know that while sexual assault is horrid no matter what, just like many other social issues, it affects different communities in different ways. this fits in beautifully with @dressember and not just because she’s wearing a dress. #dressember is a movement fighting for the dignity of all people. #metoo is fighting for a world free of sexual violence and the restoration of humanity to survivors. in her ted talk (16 minutes you won’t regret), tarana reminds us that social movements are about what is possible, not what is right now. it’s about being stronger together and supporting each other. learn the intricacies  about how these issues affect different communities in different ways. be there to understand and support survivors. be open to fighting for change. to join, go to dressember.org and click “become an advocate,” to donate follow the link in my bio.

text:
"he suggested i was using my grandmother’s death for attention. again, i decided he was probably right."
⚫
a couple of days ago i finally published a medium post (link in bio) that has been sitting in my drafts for weeks

obviously this isn't the first time i've shared a story that's personal and potentially embarrassing, but nevertheless, it was really scary to put out into the world. in the end, a few things inspired me to finally hit the big publish button

1. melanie brown's book, brutally honest @officialmelb

2. the horrible victim blaming surrounding grace millane's murder

3. megan fox saying that she was scared to share her #metoo stories because of people's perceptions of the 'perfect victim'

talking about this stuff is hard, but as i've found, bottling it up and staying silent isn't particularly healthy either

i saw a tweet yesterday that reminded me that it's important to talk about this stuff if we're in a position to do so. @poornabell wrote: "the most important thing i've learned this year, when i've wobbled, when i've gotten doubtful is that if you can, you have to use your voice to help others who cannot. i forget how many people can't articulate their tough stuff, and how listening to other people who can, helps"

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
🔥 instagram top trends de 2018
ㅤ
com 2018 quase chegando ao fim, o instagram do facebook destacou algumas tendências do ano e compartilhou todas as maneiras pelas quais a comunidade do instagram usou a plataforma para se expressar.
ㅤㅤ
de acordo com o instagram, compartilhar amor e bondade ainda é uma prioridade para a comunidade no instagram: o heart love sticker de arata foi o adesivo do giphy mais usado em stories, enquanto heart eyes foi o filtro de rosto mais usado em stories. em feed, o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado em comentários mais de 14 bilhões de vezes. o lugar mais feliz do mundo? disneyland tokyo, que também teve o maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" no texto da legenda.
ㅤ
o instagram é o lugar de inúmeros interesses e comunidades; este ano, a asmr foi a principal tendência da comunidade de nichos do ano, continuando a aumentar a sua popularidade.
ㅤ
o jogo fortnite também teve um crescimento explosivo, com a #fortnite sendo a hashtag que mais cresce no mundo. o domínio do k-pop nas mídias sociais é refletido pelo bts “army” sendo a principal comunidade de fãs na plataforma.
ㅤ
milhões de pessoas usaram o instagram para fazer suas vozes serem ouvidas em 2018. as principais hashtags do ano foram #metoo (1,5 milhão), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k).
ㅤ
ㅤㅤ
resumo de 2018 no instagram:
ㅤㅤ
● efeito de câmera mais usado no stories: heart eyes
● adesivo de gif mais usado no stories: heart love sticker por arata
● número de vezes que o emoji ❤ "coração" foi usado nos comentários: 14 bilhões
● geolocalização mais feliz no mundo (com maior uso do emoji 🙂 "sorriso" na legenda): disneyland tokyo
● principal tendência da comunidade: asmr
● hashtag com maior crescimento: #fortnite
● maior fandom: bts (#btsarmy)
● top dance movement: #inmyfeelingschallenge
● principais hashtags usadas por uma causa: #metoo (1,5 milhões), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k)
ㅤ
ㅤ

tem artigo completo lá no nosso blog:
www.bit.ly/igtop2018

would you treat a #dog this way?
_
dairy’s dark secret
the typical dairy cow on a farm produces nearly 22,000 pounds of milk a year – more than double­ what its forebears did 40 years ago. they never graze; their hooves have rotted from standing in their own filth. 
_
cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; “so common,” “seen guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‘i totally got her in the eyeball!’ it’s what happens when you do this long enough. they’re not your fellow creatures, they’re just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can’t get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. “he got sick and gave up,” and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock". it’s like they hate their own animals for having feelings.”
_

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
i will always tell, and have always told, the truth. even when my voice shakes.
•
you asking “why now” simply reveals to me that you haven’t been paying attention. “journalists” who distort the words of women to produce clickbait, who minimize their story by segmenting it and reducing it?  do better.
•
if you have chosen not to listen to the frank, clear conversations i’ve had on the topic over the last year, that’s on you. your lack of attention — to me and to all of the women who tell their stories into the void — doesn’t mean that we haven’t been screaming all along.
•
to attempt to have a field day with my life, acting like i don’t have the receipts? *you can swipe right for a selection.
•
the grace with which i’ve chosen to handle this, the deep learning i’ve done in the wake of my experience (shout out to the magnificent folks at @onsiteworkshops) that i take as sacred, and a responsibility to offer other women? do not forget that my “titanium spine,” as my sister @hilarieburton calls it, was forged in fire. i am not a woman that you will ever reduce. not one iota. none of us are. #doyougetitnow #metoo #burnitdown #timesup poem: @nayyirah.waheed

text:
do you know what happens when a child sexual abuse report is made? it may be more complicated than you think. the day we walked into a children’s advocacy center and that case number was assigned to sarah, we had no idea what was about to happen.
✨ you can read sarah’s speech describing her story at the link in the bio ➡️ who will you choose to empower.
✨ if a child ever tells you the unimaginable:
👉 know how to respond.
👉 know how to report. always dual report by calling the hotline and the local police department.
👉 make sure the child is taken to a children’s advocacy center.
💞 above all, always believe, protect, and defend the child.
#csa #defendsurvivors #traumainformedjusticesystem #childsexualabuse #notthewayitmustremain #believethechild #cac

does he ever start sentences with “i hate women who—“? does he say he wouldn’t know what to do if you ever cut your hair short? 
does he invade your privacy by reading your texts and then cry like a victim when confronted about it? does he get strangely defensive when hearing anything about the #metoo movement? 
does he get uncomfortable when you are wearing anything except a garbage bag in public? 
does he trash talk sex workers, but watch porn (that he doesn’t pay for) and did he spend his bachelor party at a strip club?

text:
de verdad es muy triste la cultura de violación en la que vivimos. cuántas personas en tu círculo social han sido violadas? y las que no sabes porque tienen miedo de hablar? yo me asombré al escuchar historias de personas muy cercanas a mí y es que siempre pensé que eso le pasaba a poca gente. ahora me doy cuenta que yo soy de las pocas que nunca sufrió una violación sexual (si dejo de lado todo el acoso sexual que viví en mi vida). de los casos que conozco ningún violador ha sido sentenciado y todavía la mara se enoja que una defienda a hacha y espada el movimiento feminista. no nos vamos a callar. nos hemos callado siglos y mira a lo que hemos llegado. el patriarcado se va a caer! #miracomonosponemos #feminism #pañueloverde #noesno

text: après 3 films hardcore, steve mcqueen (le réalisateur noir, pas l'acteur décédé) revient avec une oeuvre en plein air du temps (coucou #metoo) et de loin sa plus accessible. de la part du mec qui a fait exploser michael fassbender en prisonnier politique allant au bout de sa grève de la faim (horrible) dans hunger, puis en accro au sexe incapable de contrôler ses pulsions (glauque) dans shame, pour finir dans un film biographique sur les joies (sic) de l'esclavage aux us dans 12 years a slave, on peut sans problème avouer que les veuves surprend par sa.... sobriété :) les veuves de 4 braqueurs abattus par la police doivent prendre la relève de manière inopinée pour rembourser la dette de leurs maris décédés. de ce pitch de film d'action, mcqueen en tire une triste chronique du quotidien, qui vient sortir ses personnages principaux de leur zone de confort, les obligeant à assumer les conséquences des actes de leurs conjoints, dont elles partageaient (ou pas) le fruit de leurs actions en fermant volontairement les yeux. on est devant un très bon film de genre, au casting et à la réalisation très soignés, qui, s'il n'atteint pas les sommets des 3 précédents longs du réalisateur, se révèle de toutes façons largement au-dessus de la mêlée des films du genre. du très bon polar, à voir que vous soyez ou pas fan du réalisateur.

text:
the time i realized i was a hater...
.
.
i can honestly say i’ve taken more selfies for this account than i ever have. i use to think taking selfies said a lot about people.  i use to think it made you look conceited or like you took yourself too serious. to be 💯 i use to make fun of people that took selfies.  i mean who would wanna take pictures of themselves just to post it and see the reaction of others? at least that’s what i use to think.
.
.
i now know the real reason i didn’t take selfies, let alone post them on social media, was because i didn’t think i was worthy of them.  you see, i had a habit of shrinking in front of others because i didn’t think i was talented enough, smart enough, or good enough as everyone else.  this wasn’t just in taking selfies...this was how i felt in relationships, in doing music, in doing life.  i shrank.  i hid.  and when i did i watched others play big and step up...and then later i found myself hating on them and getting bitter and calling them selfish and full of themselves. .
.
i don’t think haters are bad people...just bitter and resentful that they shrink in front of others.  i should know...i was one.  and maybe like me they forget that they are good enough, talented enough, smart enough...more than enough.  maybe they just need reminding.  and taking a selfie doesn’t make you conceited, or full of yourself, or any of that...it just means you ain’t picture perfect but you’re worth the picture still 💜😉#imabeautifulmess
.
.

pre_proc_tweet:
the time i realized i was a hater...
.
.
i can honestly say i’ve taken more selfies for this account than i ever have. i use to think taking selfies said a lot about people.  i use to think it made you look conceited or like you took yourself too serious. to be 💯 i use to make fun of people that took selfies.  i mean who would wanna take pictures of themselves just to post it and see the reaction of others? at least that’s what i use to think.
.
.
i now know the real reason i didn’t take selfies, let alone post them on social media, was because i didn’t think i was wohy of them.  you see, i had a habit of shrinking in front of others because i didn’t think i was talented enough, sma enough, or good enough as everyone else.  this wasn’t just in taking selfies...this was how i felt in relationships, in doing music, in doing life.  i shrank.  i hid.  and when i did i watched others play big and step up...and then later i found myself hating on them and getting bitter and calling them selfish and full of themselves. .
.
i don’t think haters are bad people...just bitter and resentful that they shrink in front of others.  i should know...i was one.  and maybe like me they forget that they are good enough, talented enough, sma enough...more than enough.  maybe they just need reminding.  and taking a selfie doesn’t make you conceited, or full of yourself, or any of that...it just means you ain’t picture perfect but you’re woh the picture still 💜😉mabeautifulmess
.
.

text:
meditation workshop
|| sat dec 15 12:00-2:30pm ||
our monthly workshop this month seals off 1 year of offering this to the @breakingfreefoundation community - a community we are a part of❤ the intention is to offer an opportunity to those going through challenging times, the option to come to the workshop at no-cost. together, in community, we learn techniques which support our mental (and physical) health through evidence-based techniques which allow us to navigate our lives more peacefully, live more presently, and to connect with community as we learn these practices together.
.
we no longer offer 2 separate workshops (one at cost, one no cost). rather, we found it more impactful to create one combined group with diverse experiences. the breaking free foundation is a local non-profit organization which provides access to treatment and support to survivors of traumatic life events and experiences that said, it is not only to those healing through trauma. it open to everyone and anyone. no previous experience necessary.
.
to register, contact: info@satoriwellnessstudio.com or 403.796.9057.
.

text:
меган фокс рассказала, почему не поддерживает #metoo! 
в недавнем интервью изданию the new york times меган фокс рассказала, что не поддерживает современных голливудских феминисток и движение #metoo. актриса призналась, что неоднократно подвергалась харрасменту, однако сомневается в том, что справедливость восторжествует когда-либо. 
она также напомнила, что ещё несколько лет назад пыталась поднять эту тему, вступив в противостояние с влиятельным мужчиной. однако феминистки её не поддержали. фокс не стала подробно рассказывать о том случае, отметив, что ей многократно приходилось сталкиваться с повышенным вниманием со стороны мужчин.
стоит отметить, что несколько лет назад фокс действительно обвинила режиссёра майкла бэя в намеренной сексуализации своего образа в картине «трансформеры». тогда все от неё отмахнулись, заявив, что она наговаривает на постановщика.

text:
so many things happening around accent this weekend and all of them gooood! -
-
first off, tonight is our weekly live jazz jam! we are so thrilled to host this wonderful night of excellent music. stop on by to see some of #yegmusic’s finest talent! -
-
while you’re here, try our delicious new beer on tap, the double ipa from @apexpredatorbrewing. with only 13 kegs in the province, you’re truly sipping on a special, limited edition brew! one of #albertabeer’s finest!
-
-
if you’re looking for things to do this weekend, check out @girlbrainyeg’s holiday episode at @grindstonetheatre, featuring accent’s own @ellieheath! or stop by the sewing machine factory tonight for an awesome event, @ustogetheryeg! promoting allyship and recovery after #metoo, this event was organized by accent staff member, @miss__a___ and @brudyck (another accent alumnus) will be on the speaking panel! wow #yeg, you’re an amazing city! -
-
have a marvellous weekend, friends! see you at accent! .
.
.
.
#yegevents #yeglive #yegpeople #yeglove

text:
everyone is fighting a battle you may not see.
⚔️
i’m always inspired by the people who courageously walk their path, despite the inability of others to see the difficulties they are facing along the way.
🌋
but i also love when people bravely share their narratives to help spread awareness and encouragement.
🧡
today i’m really grateful to mika doyle for sharing a vulnerable testament to what it’s like to live with the invisible illness of ptsd. i consider myself lucky to have been able to contribute to share a few of my thoughts on the invisibility of trauma recovery in such an empowering piece.
🔗 in the bio
📸 michael bruna
.
.
.

text:
i wish you could see how perfect you are. 
i wish you could see how when you’re self conscious you cover your mouth when you’re talking and it’s adorable.  or when you laugh is a little snort.  cracks me up. 
i’m so sorry the things you’ve had to deal with alone. 
i’m so sorry you think you need to try harder and to be better and maybe then you can look in the mirror and be proud of yourself. 
because even that snarky stressed out shy version of you is beautiful. 
and after everything you’ve confronted and everything you have gotten past, and you still get up every day to take care of your family. 
things aren’t where you want to be, i get it.  they aren’t for me either.  that’s not because of what happened to you.  that not because you have more to prove than most people. 
girlfriend, when it hurts and when it’s hard you don’t have to do it alone anymore.  you are surrounded by women who know who you are and love you.  all of you. ( even the snarky stressed out bit)

reach out.  don’t separate or isolate yourself.  you don’t need to protect us from you.  we adore you. 
and when you’re ready to heal this- all of this.  i’m here.  in the meantime, we heart you.

text:
soooooo this happened today.... so many reasons for doing this

mainly because i began getting bald patches in summer of 2017 after being put on meds to help prevent diseases after being sexually assaulted by 3 evil men after going out. i couldn't eat much while on the medication so i lost a lot of weight (45ish pounds in 1.5months) and hair. after a month of not being able to look in a mirror, wear makeup or even shower really.. i became obsessed with needing to change my body. i thought if my body was different i wouldn't feel how i was feeling and it wouldn't ever happen again. i became obsessed with not gaining the weight back, i stopped eating. i self tanned more, i got bad fusion extensions and wore more and more makeup hoping it would make me feel better.. instead i destroyed my hair. the fusions ripped out huge chunks of my hair and it has never been the same. it was stringy and i had even more bald patches then before. i coloured my hair darker and left it alone for some time.... until i had an episode this summer and decided to completely ruin it with a "semi" blue dye. after that ordeal it was a mess, it felt awful. basically it was really unhealthy for the last 2 years. i also continuously get hives from stress on my scalp and lately it's been super uncomfortable, i couldn't take it anymore. i've also been struggling with my self care ever since the assault... i feel like seeing my face and not having hair to hid behind all the time will push me to be more accountable for my self care habits (hello skincare!!!). i need change!!!!! and slowly but surely i'm getting there... recently i cut it into a pixie and weeks ago i made the decision to shave it but today my friend at school did it for me! i've never felt better and my scalp can finally chill and breathe.

thanks everyone for the constant support through my recovery i'm finding my way along ❤love to everyone.
if you've been through something similar i'm always here to talk! the #metoo movement is real and serious ladies. always be careful going out!!

we got permission to write the english text on her film, to make all understand. how many thousands of innocent women are imprisoned in dar al reaya prisons for young women around saudi. the charges for being there can be ”escaping” from an abusive guardian or ”disobeying” the guardian or being raped!! there is no other way out of hell than marrying another guardian, a stranger, that dar al reaya picks for them. they get lashed every week. we have had eye witnesses, victims who have been inside tell us what it was like and what girls go theough trying to escape these places... its about time dar al reaya is exposed for what it is. since this film was made seven new dar al reaya prisons opened in the kingdom. #daralreaya #metoo #stopenslavingsaudiwomen #endmaleguardianship #iammyownguardian #feminism #thisiswhatafeministlookslike #womenswave #womentogether #unwomen #humanrightswatch #hrw #hbv #honorviolence #saudiarabia #ksa #metoo #timesup #hbv #honor #honorkilling #saudiarabia

text: "sexual harassment exists in a pyramid that’s foundation is built upon objectification and offensive remarks, and at the top of the pyramid is rape and assault. we can’t talk about harassment without talking about all gender-based violence. we can’t “solve” sexual harassment without addressing the entire pyramid. the film examines the ways in which our legal system can fail victims, the way we socialize our girls and boys differently as well as the way the brain reacts to trauma and taking a look at the long term effects of these behaviors." read up on director sarah moshman's background and what she's learned so far making nevertheless! link in bio #nevertheless #metoo #timesup

text:
▪️human, too.▪️
“your scars are a warning to all future monsters, of the hell you have survived before them, every demon you have vanquished and every battle you have won.” @nikita_gill ▪️
i reached my breaking point this year and held fast, stood strong and reached further. this is my story. (link in bio.) it doesn’t represent all women’s experiences... but it is representative of a toxic culture that is pervasive in our everyday lives and even, unfortunately, our churches.
▪️
i won a few battles this year, vanquished a lot of demons in my life, all with the help of an advocate who goes before me. and i am stronger than i ever was before. as @hannah_gadsby  says, “there is no way, there is no way any one would dare, dare test their strength out on me. because you all know, there is nothing stronger than a broken woman who has rebuilt herself.”
▪️
and so... i finish out 2018 with a renewed purpose, ready to rise up and face any monsters who come my way in 2019. blog link in bio. #anoutlier #outlierblog #metoo #churchtoo

text:
karina longworth's dulcet tones have moved from the radio waves to the page with the release of her new book "seduction: sex, lies and stardom in howard hughes' hollywood". the host of the wildly popular podcast, 'you must remember this' takes the research from her first few radio series to expose the pillars of misogyny and exploitation the golden age of american cinema was built upon. harvey weinstein and #metoo come as no surprise to a film historian well versed in the deep currents of exploitation and obsession that the legacy of a hedonistic old hollywood still endures nearly a century later. hollywood babylon and the legends of chateau marmont come alive in this compelling, meticulously researched read to devour over the christmas period. .
.
.
.

text:
not sure if i will be completing new work by years end so...it's been one hell of a year and i just want to say thank you all who have ordered, supported, hated, followed, loved, unfollowed, helped and criticised me and my artwork this year. every piece i create comes from your minds and mine. every tedious hour is practice put in. every #painting is a statement and a #milestone that aspires #realism. every work becomes a memory for me and a welcome from your home. i will improve more and more as i go. thank you all for the commission work. thank you for keeping me and the art alive. ten...hell, even four years ago, i didn't even think that id be able to do any #portrait work. now i can't imagine not doing it. always believe in yourselves. cheesy, but truth.
i'll be posting varnish and progress posts but most likely no new complete works this month. happy new year and may you all find your artistic purpose in this life. blessings. 🙏 #whoisharo
.
.
.

text:
app-elles is a free safety app for all women and girls who are victims of violence. it meets the main support needs for women faced with violence. it offers, in a simple and intuitive interface, three features : warning, calling and searching for help. 
app-elles enables users to quickly alert and easily call friends, family, emergency services, ngos and any revelant contacts. its additional bracelet is connected to an innovative streaming protocol: live and recorded audio streaming, instant replay feature and gps tracking in real time. 
all together, we can fight against violence by using solidarity, mutual help and reciprocal vigilance. to join, download app-elles for free, use it and share it around.💜💜💜 #app_elles #resonantes #againstviolenceagainstwomen #metoo #wearetryingtochangetheworld #wat2ctw

text:
あのね、たとえ寂しくても、全ての人類を受け入れる必要はないよ。
この人には会いたいけど、この人はダメとか、個人単位で選り好みしていい。それは別に贅沢じゃない。
あと、時々の気分でそれが、変わってもいい。みんなそうだから。

even if you are lonely, you do not have to accept all humanity. we'd like to meet this person, but this person is ok, we can choose it by per individual. it's not extravagant.
also, it can change with the mood sometimes. because everyone is so.

#metoo #remetoo #praisethebrave #bubbleoff

text:
según la l#ey
- #acososexual
- #abusosexual: abuso sexual simple o abuso gravemente ultrajante
- #violacion

para identificar uno de los otros, sugiero leer sobre ello. todas son situaciones íncómodas donde hay un #abusodeepoder y #autoridad . 
ser besada o acorralada para ser besada cuando niña por personas ajenas a mi familia y mucho mayor que yo, por ejemplo. ser tocada en los trasportes y en los boliches o ser dicho las más ingeniosas barbaridades sexuales en la calle y otros ámbitos. 
de las situaciones cuando niña, en parte me he escapado/escabullido. estas situaciones se daban por personas no familiares en reuniones familiares. hoy sé que los actores me la dejaron pasar también ya que me excedían en edad y masa física como para hacer más. y desde adolescente hasta hace unos pocos años atrás, me he defendido con la palabra de la manera más hiriente hacia el agresor o agresores. algunos se bajaban del transporte con una previa batalla discursiva, otros en la calle seguían de largo callados y hubo quien comenzó a tirarme piedras. 
agradezco mi #fuerza y mi carácter. aún así fue muy cansador. hace unos pocos años que, a la par y quizás como consecuencia, al ir reconociendo las situaciones, el por qué y mis propias energías, algo cambió. poner #límites y expresar mi #deseo es más fácil como así propiciar la charla. puedo tomarme el tiempo hasta que la emocionalidad merme y conversar sobre lo que nos incomoda. hasta donde se quiere y puede.

comparto un poco de lo vivido porque me hace bien y porque acompaña. esto que publico ya he lo conversado con otras personas. la escucha es muy importante, darnos un espacio para abordarlo es sanador y más al sentirnos acompañados.

éste es mi yo también. y sos bienvenid@ para compartir también.

más abrazos 💗
mariela

text:
claudia guebel, la empleada del congreso que denunció en la justicia al senador juan carlos marino por abuso sexual, habló por primera vez en los medios y dio detalles de la situación que vivió en el despacho del legislador radical pampeano. “ sin mediar palabra, el tipo avanzó a manosearme los pechos. no viene al caso decir cómo estaba vestida. pero yo cuido mucho el vestuario. tengo un exceso de formalidad. era insólito que metiera la mano por debajo de un saco de sastre. me quedé atónita, temblorosa, con miedo", recordó guebel, quien lleva dos décadas como empleada en la cámara alta y "más de 30 años de militancia" en la ucr. "espero que esto sea un antes y un después para las mujeres que trabajan en política", agregó conmovida. 
#metoo #argentina #noesno #miracomomeponemos

text:
"please, stop haunting me"

it's been a year and a half since i started having nightmares with a person who made me so much damage for some years and the last thing he did was harassing me sexually. 
even though i've been going to therapy since last january with a psychologist and a few months later with a psychiatrist, nightmares where he chases me and haunts me haven't stopped.

i get very anxious when i go out because we live in a city that is not very big, and the chances of being in the same place at the same time are big.

i drew this two weeks ago, and last night i had nightmares again.

sometimes this seems like it's never going to end.
.
.

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
un regalo pa las pibas
.
tattoo iconography for decades has being shown women objectification. during this week, i have been reading and listening women testimonies of abuse that has come up as a result of  #miracomonosponemos and i thought my duty with this cause is to change that iconography in something that represents us. i’m a visual artist, i don't use words, those are my tools to express myself. a mis compatriotas, estoy lejos pero a la vez muy cerca, esto es para ustedes y por nosotras. con las pibas siempre!💚✊🏼

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
alert only the ones you know!

app-elles is a free safety app for all women and girls who are victims of violence. it meets the main support needs for women faced with violence. it offers, in a simple and intuitive interface, three features : warning, calling and searching for help. 
app-elles enables users to quickly alert and easily call friends, family, emergency services, ngos and any revelant contacts. its additional bracelet is connected to an innovative streaming protocol: live and recorded audio streaming, instant replay feature and gps tracking in real time. 
all together, we can fight against violence by using solidarity, mutual help and reciprocal vigilance. to join, download app-elles for free, use it and share it around.💜💜💜 #app_elles #resonantes #againstviolenceagainstwomen #metoo #wearetryingtochangetheworld #wat2ctw

ben monterroso, executive director of mi familia vota, issued the following statement: “the death of a child in u.s. custody is unacceptable. as a parent, my heart is torn for the father of jakelin amei rosemary caal maquin. as a citizen, i am outraged that our country operates with systems not designed to uphold basic human rights, and leadership who minimizes the value of life by continuing to tolerate these deaths. president trump and republicans have continuously stopped efforts to bring immigration reform and these are the results of their actions. “it’s time for introspection and action. we must recognize that our current approach to migrants is ethically flawed; we have to start with the premise that migrant lives are valuable, because they are. the migrant camps, detention centers, and holding cells are incompatible with human needs. furthermore, there are repeated reports of abuse, lack of medical care, and extreme organizational incapacity to properly run these operations. now is the time to end these practices, to defund these institutions, which have not been able to meet basic living standards, and to look for solutions that work in a way that upholds our national values. “we are the most powerful country in the world, we can keep migrant children alive. we call on congress to pass legislation that will end operations that put immigrant lives at risk and end the impunity that is allotted to agencies that interact with immigrants. as a community, we have to commit to monitoring our elected officials’ responses to this tragedy and ensure that they bring forth and pass laws that can resolve immigration needs while avoiding deaths. statements and condolences are not justice for little jakelin.” #justiceforjakelin

text:
#miracomonosponemos 
el movimiento de mujeres de #argentina viene luchando hace años contra diferentes tipos de violencias (#niunamenos) e inequidades de género, haciéndole frente al patriarcado en todas sus formas y reclamando más derechos (como el #abortolegal ). luego de la denuncia pública de las actrices, muchas mujeres lograron animarse a ponerle voz a experiencias terribles de abusos que habían sufrido y callado durante años. compartimos ésta imagen porque el campo cultural lejos de estar exento de violencias, abusos e inequidades es un espacio desde donde visibilizarlo y transformarlo.
#sevaacaer porque lo vamos a tirar!
#noesno en todos los idiomas.

argentines speaks out against sexual abuse after a brave young actress @soythelmafardin reported that she was raped by an actor colegue when she was 16 and he was 45. 'enough, we won't remain silent any longer' claimed @actrices.argentinas women's rights movement unite to fight against all types of gender violence and encourage women to report abuses in all fields. #empoweringwomen #futureisfemale #metoo

les argentines mobilisées face à la violence machiste. les #femmes unit en la lutte pour demander la fin des violences basées sur le #genre et réclamer à la société une prise de conscience de l'aspect systémique de cette violence. #egalite 💚 ✊ @gal.productora.cultural
ilustración @luisa_ilustra

text: #maryloupavlovic blast from the past. "liar!" 2004 this was a large street poster i made  after over 20 australian women came forward accusing footballers  of sexual assault. there was not one conviction later i found that domestic violence increased on grand final day. i couldn't believe that women were being treated like this in a so-called democracy and that these male football stars who were celebrated at the center of the community were blatantly allowed to get away with assault. i dressed up as a football fan with a black eye. i put up 250 of these posters around melbourne for two weeks around the time of the afl grand final 2004. we still have so much further to go. sometime later i visited bali and my work became what it is now, like a ship turning and altering its course. #feministart #womensart #protestart #contemporaryart #metoo #violenceagainstwomen #earlywork #streetart #streetposterart #artbywomen

text:
i look in the mirror to see lines
in my face.
the movies tell me 
i ought to be worried.
advertisements promise 
creams to smooth it all away.
but life experience causes me 
to sigh in relief.
“fewer gazes will follow me now” i say to myself -- and i feel safer already. - the reality of being female
.
.
.

——家父

text:
app-elles is a free safety app for all women and girls who are victims of violence. it meets the main support needs for women faced with violence. it offers, in a simple and intuitive interface, three features : warning, calling and searching for help.

app-elles enables users to quickly alert and easily call friends, family, emergency services, ngos and any revelant contacts. its additional bracelet is connected to an innovative streaming protocol: live and recorded audio streaming, instant replay feature and gps tracking in real time. 
all together, we can fight against violence by using solidarity, mutual help and reciprocal vigilance. to join, download app-elles for free, use it and share it around.💜💜💜 #app_elles #resonantes #againstviolenceagainstwomen #metoo #wearetryingtochangetheworld #wat2ctw

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

text:
обнаружено самое счастливое место на планете

сотрудники социальной сети instagram проанализировали поставленные пользователями смайлики, геолокации и хештеги и опубликовали итоги 2018 года. 
как передает media.az, об этом сообщается на официальном сайте instagram.

таким образом, самой счастливой геолокацией instagram признал диснейленд в токио, так как больше всего счастливых смайликов в 2018 году пользователи ставили именно под фотографиями из японского диснейленда.

также эксперты назвали самый популярный фильтр для лица: им стал фильтр с сердечками на глазах. а, например, самыми часто используемыми хештегами в 2018 году были #metoo, #timesup и #marchforourlives.

в ноябре сотрудники британской ассоциации потребителей which? составили рейтинг самых безопасных стран для путешествий. специалисты проанализировали 20 самых популярных туристических направлений по четырем критериям: уровень преступности, угроза здоровью, вероятность теракта и стихийных бедствий. самой безопасной страной по всем параметрам стала исландия.

text:
16/12/2018
jaipur

assembling for candle march and street play in the memory of ‘nirbhaya’ on 16 th of december, 2016, at statue circle, jaipur by rang mastaaney.

on date 16th of december, rang mastaaney- a theatre group of young artists, is organising a peaceful ‘candle march ‘ at 5 pm in evening from central park towards statue circle in the name and memory of ‘nirbhaya‘- and afterwards , we will perform a  street play (nukkad natak) – ‘abb bass’ on women empowerment and eve teasing, at statue circle, jaipur .

we are performing this street play since 2012, after the tragic incident of gang rape of the brave girl ‘nirbhaya’ in the capital on 16 of december, 2012. since then, rang mastaaney is actively engaged in this cause and has performed 900 plus shows of nukkad at various places in jaipur city, viz; malls, schools, colleges, institutions, markets and festivals.
our aim is to make people aware about the atrocities and wrongdoing happening to the women and girls all across the country

we as an active theatre group, has conducted many workshop for students to help them achieve and learn various aspects of theatre and drama and make them the part of our cause.

dated- 16 december, 2018
timings -: candle march - 5 pm to 5:30 pm
street play - 5:30 pm onwards.
venue: statue circle, jaipur. 
rang mastaney 
abhishek mudgal (director)
9413115285

#nirbhaya  #meetoo #gangrape  #womenatrocities  #stautecircle #rangnastaaney #streetplay #abbass #16december  #againstrape  #metoo  #metoomovement

text:
two weeks ago my father killed himself the night before the court could have found him guilty for abusing me as a child in the age of 2,5 till 5. it took me decades to speak up, it took me years to walk through these hearings, it took pages over pages in appraisals to prove my credibility, it took so many stays in mental hospitals... years within i was suicidal as well. at the bottom of all my mind... totally lost... and in the end there will be only another shocking kind of pain. i won and lost everything at the same time, when he decided to confess his offenses with this final cut... he paid blood with blood. that's what i never wanted... i wanted him to take responsibility for me as his daugther and for no longer being his victim. my inner child always missed a father, she never had. so she does by now... and forever.

a melody of my soul for a dead dad...
https://youtu.be/njdmjwja0i0

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and tre
